review_blob: This is what you drink when you are broke. It is also a good choice for those that "dont drink beer", because it is extremely light in body and easy to drink, guzzle, or funnel. During Spring Break around here it sells for around $12 per 30-can "cube". You really have to factor that in, it is really, really cheap and really, really "unoffensive". This is for college kids who have no money but still want to get drunk. The ultimate econo-beer.

I actually like tomato/clamato with my beer every once in a while, but this is utterly disgusting. I had 3 large sips and had to throw the rest away. Ive never been unable to finish a beer due to taste before. The aroma is funky - and the overall taste is just bad. fishy/salty/flat/metallic/rotten egg.
